<DocsLayout title="Error Handling in Slumber" sidebar={slumberSidebar} description="How Slumber reports errors with path tracking and graceful degradation">

<h1>Error Handling</h1>

<p class="text-xl text-gray-400 !mt-2 !mb-8">
  Slumber's two-pass strategy gives you speed when things work and precision when they don't.
</p>

<h2>The two-pass strategy</h2>

<p>When you call <code>codec.awake()</code>, two things happen:</p>

<ol>
  <li><strong>Fast pass</strong> — Deserializes with no path tracking. Minimal overhead. If it succeeds, you're done.</li>
  <li><strong>Tracking pass</strong> — Only runs if the fast pass throws. Re-deserializes with full path tracking, collecting diagnostic information at every level.</li>
</ol>

<p>This means you pay zero cost for path tracking in the success case — which is the common case.</p>

<h2>Nullable vs non-nullable errors</h2>

<p>The key design decision: <strong>nullable fields absorb errors, non-nullable fields report them</strong>.</p>

<Code code={`data class Profile(val name: String, val bio: String?)

// Non-nullable field with bad data → AwakerException
codec.awake<Profile>(mapOf("name" to listOf(1, 2, 3), "bio" to "hello"))
// → AwakerException: "Value at path 'root.name' must not be null"

// Nullable field with bad data → graceful null
codec.awake<Profile>(mapOf("name" to "Alice", "bio" to listOf(1, 2, 3)))
// → Profile(name="Alice", bio=null)   ← no crash`} lang="kotlin" theme="vitesse-dark" />

<h2>Path tracking in nested structures</h2>

<p>Error messages include the full path to the failing field:</p>

<Code code={`data class Address(val zip: String)
data class Company(val address: Address)
data class Employee(val company: Company)

codec.awake<Employee>(mapOf(
    "company" to mapOf(
        "address" to mapOf(
            "zip" to null  // null for non-nullable String
        )
    )
))
// → AwakerException: "Value at path 'root.company.address.zip' must not be null"`} lang="kotlin" theme="vitesse-dark" />

<h2>Collection index in error paths</h2>

<p>When an error occurs inside a collection, the index is included in the path:</p>

<Code code={`data class Container(val items: List<Int>)

codec.awake<Container>(mapOf(
    "items" to listOf(1, null, 3)
))
// → AwakerException: "Value at path 'root.items.1' must not be null"
//                                              ^ index 1`} lang="kotlin" theme="vitesse-dark" />

<h2>Missing required parameters</h2>

<p>When a non-nullable, non-default parameter is missing from the input:</p>

<Code code={`data class User(val name: String, val age: Int)

codec.awake<User>(mapOf("name" to "Alice"))
// → AwakerException with message containing:
//   "Value at path 'root' must not be null"
//   "'root': User misses parameters 'age'"`} lang="kotlin" theme="vitesse-dark" />

<h2>Exception types</h2>

<p>Slumber defines three exception classes:</p>

<Code code={`// Base class for all Slumber errors
open class SlumberException(message: String) : Throwable(message)

// Thrown when deserialization fails
class AwakerException(
    message: String,
    val logs: List<String>,     // Diagnostic messages from nested levels
    val rootType: KType?,       // The type being deserialized
    val input: Any?,            // The input data that caused the error
) : SlumberException(message)

// Thrown when serialization fails (e.g. null for non-nullable type)
class SlumbererException(
    message: String,
    val input: Any?,            // The data that caused the error
) : SlumberException(message)`} lang="kotlin" theme="vitesse-dark" />

<h2>Catching and handling errors</h2>

<Code code={`try {
    val user = codec.awake<User>(untrustedData)
} catch (e: AwakerException) {
    println("Deserialization failed at: extracted from message")
    println("Root type: ${'$'}{e.rootType}")
    println("Input: ${'$'}{e.input}")
    println("Diagnostics: ${'$'}{e.logs.joinToString("\\n")}")
}`} lang="kotlin" theme="vitesse-dark" />

<h2>Default parameter fallback</h2>

<p>When a field has a default value and the input provides invalid data, the default is used:</p>

<Code code={`data class Config(
    val host: String = "localhost",
    val port: Int = 8080,
)

// Invalid data for "port" → falls back to default
codec.awake<Config>(mapOf("host" to "myserver", "port" to "not_a_number"))
// → Config(host="myserver", port=8080)`} lang="kotlin" theme="vitesse-dark" />

